<Markdown>
## Your Turn: Johnny's ABCs

Using the story about Johnny, explain the sequence of **Antecedent**, **Behavior**, and **Consequence** in your own words.

_Recall: Annie's roommate tells Johnny to get into bed, but he runs away from the room laughing whenever "bed" is mentioned. The roommate chases after him and keeps nagging him to go to bed._
</Markdown>

<TextArea id="fba2_abc_johnny_explanation" rows="4" placeholder="Describe the Antecedent, Behavior, and Consequence for Johnny's bedtime situation..." />

<ActionButton id="fba2_abc_johnny_check_btn" label="Check My Understanding" dependsOn="@fba2_abc_johnny_explanation.value">
<LLMAction id="fba2_abc_johnny_check" target="fba2_abc_johnny_feedback"><![CDATA[
A psychology student was asked to identify the ABCs (Antecedent, Behavior, Consequence)
for this scenario: Annie's roommate tells Johnny to get into bed, but he runs away from
the room laughing. The roommate chases after him and keeps nagging him to go to bed.

The correct answer is:
- Antecedent: Roommate tells Johnny to go to bed
- Behavior: Johnny runs out of the room laughing
- Consequence: Roommate chases after him / he avoids going to bed on time

Here is the student's response:
]]>
<Ref id="fba2_ref_abc_johnny" target="fba2_abc_johnny_explanation" />
<![CDATA[
