specific about what they got right and what needs correction. Keep it brief.
]]></LLMAction>
</ActionButton>

<LLMFeedback id="fba2_abc_johnny_feedback" render="markdown" />
</Vertical>


<HH> ============= Screen: Johnny's function ==================== </HH>

<Vertical id="fba2_johnny_function">
<MarkupProblem id="fba2_johnny_function_choice" title="Function of Johnny's Behavior"><![CDATA[
## What is the function of Johnny's behavior?

>>Now that you've identified the ABCs of Johnny's bedtime behavior, what is the function of his running out of the room?<<

( ) Access to preferred activity/object
( ) Attention
(x) Escape
( ) Sensory

[explanation]
The function is **escape**. Johnny's running away is maintained by negative reinforcement — he successfully avoids or delays going to bed (the aversive event). The antecedent (being told to go to bed) triggers the behavior (running away), and the consequence (not having to go to bed right away) reinforces it.
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>
</Vertical>


<HH> ============= Screen: Competing Behavior Pathway (blank) === </HH>

<Vertical id="fba2_competing_pathway_blank">
<Markdown>
## Competing Behavior Pathway

Use the color-coded reference diagram below to understand the Competing Behavior Pathway. Then fill in each part for Johnny's bedtime scenario.
</Markdown>

<Mermaid id="fba2_pathway_reference" src="diagrams/cbp_blank_template.mmd" />

<Markdown>
### Fill in the Competing Behavior Pathway for Johnny

The antecedent has been filled in for you. Complete the rest based on what you know about Johnny's bedtime situation.
</Markdown>

<Markdown>**Antecedent** (what happens before the problem behavior): **Roommate tells Johnny to go to bed**</Markdown>

<Markdown>**Problem Behavior** (what Johnny does):</Markdown>
<TextArea id="fba2_pathway_behavior" rows="1" placeholder="What does Johnny do?" />

<Markdown>**Consequence** (what happens after the behavior):</Markdown>
<TextArea id="fba2_pathway_consequence" rows="1" placeholder="What does the roommate do in response?" />

<Markdown>**Function** (why does this behavior continue?):</Markdown>
<TextArea id="fba2_pathway_function" rows="1" placeholder="What function does this behavior serve?" />

<ActionButton id="fba2_pathway_check_btn" label="Check My Pathway" dependsOn="@fba2_pathway_behavior.value">
